===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|weder}}, {{m|enm|wedir}}, from {{inh|en|ang|weder}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*wedrą}}, from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*wedʰrom}} (={{m|ine-pro|*we-dʰrom}}). Cognate with {{cog|stq|Weeder}}, {{cog|fy|waar}}, {{cog|nl|weer}}, {{cog|nds|Weder}}, {{cog|de|Wetter}}, {{cog|da|vejr}}, {{cog|sv|väder}}, {{cog|is|veður}}; also more distantly related to Russian {{m|ru|вёдро||fair weather|tr=vjodro}} and perhaps Albanian {{m|sq|vrëndë||light rain}}.

